{"id":56,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":56,"title":"Chapter 52: The Destruction of the Jaredites","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 52","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 52"],["h1","The Destruction of the Jaredites"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p3"},"The Jaredites grew in number and became rich. They chose a king to be their leader."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/6.18,22,27-28"},"Ether 6:18, 22, 27–28"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p5"},"Many years passed, and the Jaredites became wicked. The Lord sent prophets to tell them to repent or they would be destroyed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/11.1"},"Ether 11:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p7"},"The people did not listen to the prophets. They tried to kill them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/11.2"},"Ether 11:2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p9"},"There were wars and famines in the land. Many Jaredites died."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/11.7"},"Ether 11:7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p11"},"The Lord sent another prophet, named Ether. He preached from morning until evening, telling the Jaredites to believe in God and repent."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/12.2-3"},"Ether 12:2–3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p13"},"Ether told the Jaredites that if they would believe in God, they would someday live with Heavenly Father in a better world."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/12.4"},"Ether 12:4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p15"},"Ether told the Jaredites many important things, but they did not believe him. They made him leave the city."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/12.5"},"Ether 12:5"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/13.13"},"Ether 13:13"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p17"},"Ether hid in a cave during the day so he would not be killed. At night he went out and saw what was happening to the Jaredites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/13.13-14"},"Ether 13:13–14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p19"},"He finished writing the history of the Jaredites while he was hiding."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/13.14"},"Ether 13:14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p21"},"The Lord sent Ether to Coriantumr, who was a wicked Jaredite king. Ether told him to repent or he would live to see all his people killed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/13.16-17,20-21"},"Ether 13:16–17, 20–21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p23"},"Coriantumr and his people did not repent. He tried to have Ether killed, but Ether ran and hid in the cave."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/13.22"},"Ether 13:22"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p25"},"The people were so wicked that the Lord cursed the land. They could not set their tools or swords down because by the next day the objects would be gone."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/14.1"},"Ether 14:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p27"},"All the Jaredites fought in the wars, including the women and children. Coriantumr led one army and a man named Shiz led the other."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/14.19-20"},"Ether 14:19–20"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/15.15"},"Ether 15:15"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p29"},"Coriantumr and Shiz were both wicked men. The Holy Ghost had left the Jaredites because of their wickedness. Satan had full power over them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/15.19"},"Ether 15:19"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p31"},"The Jaredites fought until Coriantumr and Shiz were the only ones left. When Shiz fainted from losing so much blood, Coriantumr cut off his head."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/15.29-30"},"Ether 15:29–30"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p33"},"Ether’s prophecy had come true: Coriantumr was the last Jaredite alive. He was found by the people of Zarahemla."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/omni/1.21"},"Omni 1:21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_056_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p35"},"Ether finished writing the history of the Jaredites. They had been destroyed because of their wickedness. The Jaredite records were later found by the Nephites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-52-the-destruction-of-the-jaredites.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/15.33"},"Ether 15:33"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
